title: Saints Stifle Knights for Homecoming Win
text:
Saints Stifle Knights for Homecoming Win 
By Norman Seawright III October 3, 2015 Updated Oct 3, 2015 at 10:57 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) -- The St. Scholastica (CSS) football team laid waste to Upper Midwest Athletic Conference opponent Martin Luther for the Saints' Homecoming weekend at Malosky Stadium. 
The Saints used three quarterbacks in the 53-13 blowout; Kyle Stepka went 4-for-6, and scored two touchdowns. Earl Butler went 3-for-7 and scored a touchdown. Mike Mensing was 2-for-3.
